body_html:
Hmmm, not sure I see the actual error message there :/

Questions:

  • What happens if you try to execute external/androidndk/ndk/toolchains/arm-linux-androideabi-4.9/prebuilt/linux-x86_64/bin/arm-linux-androideabi-ar by itself?
  • Have you attempted to compile without the native code change?
  • Do you have enough disk space/memory for the VM?

FWIW, we have a similar internal change that will hopefully be out in the next push or two to change the default detector to a multi-class model using the TF Object Detection api, so you should be able to use the prebuilt .so binaries then without any edits.

body:
Hmmm, not sure I see the actual error message there :/ 

Questions:
- What happens if you try to execute `external/androidndk/ndk/toolchains/arm-linux-androideabi-4.9/prebuilt/linux-x86_64/bin/arm-linux-androideabi-ar` by itself?
- Have you attempted to compile without the native code change?
- Do you have enough disk space/memory for the VM?

FWIW, we have a similar internal change that will hopefully be out in the next push or two to change the default detector to a multi-class model using the TF Object Detection api, so you should be able to use the prebuilt .so binaries then without any edits.
